Node.Notes: To tremble with emotion, could be anger or fear here. If anger, sense is be angry, but don't sin! (in other words, if you are angry, do not sin).
Seems to say you can tremble with anger, but don't sin by acting out of rage.
Seems to be advice to speak evil words within hearts while in your beds, not out loud elsewhere, where you could do harm.
Unusual construction, but probably connects in sense of "I will both lay down and sleep in peace."
